mits, scope changes, carry-forward links.\\n  3. Build a summary context string.\\n  4. Embed a query like \\\"patterns in this team's last 4 weeks\\\" and query Pinecone for historical context.\\n  5. Send to AiProviderRegistry with type \\\"TEAM_INSIGHT\\\" — system prompt asks for 3-5 actionable management insights, each citing specific plans/commits/tickets.\\n  6. Parse structured response: `{ insights: [{ insightText, severity, sourceEntityIds, actionSuggestion }] }`.\\n  7. Store each insight via the new `AiSuggestionService.storeSuggestion()` overload (from step-1), passing `teamId=teamId` and `weekStartDate=weekStartDate`. Set `suggestion_type = 'TEAM_INSIGHT'`, `planId = null`, `userId = null`. This persists the team+week identity directly in the `ai_suggestion` row so the read endpoint can query `findByTeamIdAndWeekStartDateAndSuggestionType(teamId, weekStartDate, \\\"TEAM_INSIGHT\\\")`.\\n- Public method `void generatePersonalInsights(UUID planId)` — Loads the plan, gathers its commits/scope-changes/carry-forwards. Embeds a query like \\\"patterns for this user's recent plans\\\" and queries Pinecone for the user's historical context (filter by userId). Sends to LLM with type \\\"PERSONAL_INSIGHT\\\". Stores each insight via `AiSuggestionService.storeSuggestion()` with `planId=planId`, `userId=plan.ownerUserId`, `teamId=plan.teamId`, `weekStartDate=plan.weekStartDate`, and `suggestion_type='PERSONAL_INSIGHT'`. This is called from two places:\\n  1. **On plan lock** — `LockService.lockPlan()` calls `insightGenerationService.generatePersonalInsightsAsync(planId)` (hook added in step-5). The `@Async` annotation ensures it doesn't block the lock transaction.\\n  2. **Daily scheduled job** — `generateDailyInsights()` iterates all teams, generates team insights, and also generates personal insights for each LOCKED plan in the current week that doesn't already have PERSONAL_INSIGHT rows (idempotency check via `findByPlanIdAndSuggestionType(planId, \\\"PERSONAL_INSIGHT\\\")`). This catches plans that were locked while Pinecone/LLM was unavailable.\\n- `@Async public void generatePersonalInsightsAsync(UUID planId)` — Thin async wrapper that calls `generatePersonalInsights(planId)` inside a try/catch (graceful degradation). This is the method LockService calls.\\n- Add \\\"TEAM_INSIGHT\\\" and \\\"PERSONAL_INSIGHT\\\" type constants to AiContext.\\n\\nCreate prompt templates:\\n- `backend/src/main/resources/prompts/team-insight.txt`\\n- `backend/src/main/resources/prompts/personal-insight.txt`\\n\\nUpdate `StubAiProvider.java` to handle TEAM_INSIGHT and PERSONAL_INSIGHT with canned responses.\\n\\nCreate `backend/src/test/java/com/weeklycommit/ai/rag/InsightGenerationServiceTest.java`:\\n- Unit test with mocked dependencies.\\n- Test team insight generation stores correct number of suggestions with teamId and weekStartDate set.\\n- Test personal insight generation stores with planId, userId, teamId, weekStartDate set.\\n- Test personal insight idempotency (skips if suggestions already exist for the plan).\\n- Test unavailable Pinecone skips gracefully.\\n- Test scheduled job iterates teams and generates both team + personal insights.\",\n  \"requiredChecks\": [\n    \"build\",\n    \"unit\"\n  ]\n}\n\nYou are the first agent to work on this step.\nImplement the changes described above, run checks to verify, and fix any issues before handing off.\nBe thorough — the next agent will review your work and should find it correct.\n\nWhen done, explain what you reviewed, what you changed (if anything), and your assessment.\n\nEnd with:\nVerdict: approve  — if the step is complete and correct, no more changes needed\nVerdict: changes_made  — if you made fixes or improvements\nVerdict: replan_needed  — if the step is structurally impossible to complete as planned and needs controller-managed replanning"}],"timestamp":1774502917364}}
